01:06:25.849 --> 01:06:28.477
Yeah, with the flow!

01:06:31.154 --> 01:06:32.485
How is it?

01:06:35.425 --> 01:06:38.087
Wow! Fantastic!

01:06:38.194 --> 01:06:41.493
Right, my turn!
Quality entertainment coming up!

01:07:00.250 --> 01:07:02.377
Got one!

01:07:02.485 --> 01:07:04.453
Nishi!

01:08:41.484 --> 01:08:45.078
Nishi, remember when we found a stray dog?

01:08:45.488 --> 01:08:46.921
In kindergarten?

01:08:47.524 --> 01:08:50.287
And you said you'd take care of it?

01:08:50.827 --> 01:08:53.352
That made me so happy!

01:08:53.462 --> 01:08:54.930
Yeah?

01:08:55.532 --> 01:08:58.524
I'm gonna take him home with me.

01:08:58.902 --> 01:09:01.462
You will? Thank you!

01:09:01.571 --> 01:09:05.029
I already have a sea-monkey, so it'll be fine!

01:09:06.509 --> 01:09:10.673
Wanna see? C'mon, I'll show ya!

01:09:11.214 --> 01:09:12.442
Myon.

01:09:13.683 --> 01:09:15.582
So this is the new plot!

01:09:16.386 --> 01:09:18.216
In the far, distant future,

01:09:18.321 --> 01:09:22.814
where the world is starving from
over-population and environmental destruction,

01:09:23.626 --> 01:09:27.790
Earth decides to send
a spaceship in search of food.

01:09:31.600 --> 01:09:33.535
But something goes wrong.

01:09:36.206 --> 01:09:38.197
They land on a strange planet.

01:09:38.308 --> 01:09:43.041
There's water and oxygen,
but nothing edible for humans!

01:09:46.549 --> 01:09:49.211
Except for one thing, they soon discover:

01:09:54.557 --> 01:09:57.617
A certain creature's pooh.

01:09:58.761 --> 01:10:00.126
Oh, gross!

01:10:01.497 --> 01:10:03.631
And it's the perfect food for humans.

01:10:03.666 --> 01:10:04.894
<i>"It's delicious!"
And it's the perfect food for humans.</i>

01:10:06.903 --> 01:10:10.634
But the creature's unbelievably bad at hunting
and on the verge of extinction!

01:10:10.807 --> 01:10:12.331
There's only one?

01:10:13.643 --> 01:10:17.340
Our men help the creature hunt, look after it!

01:10:17.847 --> 01:10:22.546
And they live like that for a while
until a new enemy arrives.

01:10:23.553 --> 01:10:28.388
Higher species of plants begin to fight
for food, which is also creature chips!

01:10:28.491 --> 01:10:30.322
A pooh-war, huh?

01:10:30.860 --> 01:10:33.920
But what happens then? The crew?

01:10:35.898 --> 01:10:39.026
Guess we need to send them home safely, huh?

01:10:39.535 --> 01:10:42.993
The planet is ideal in its own way, but...

01:10:44.507 --> 01:10:48.705
In fact, the planet's some kind of cell!

01:10:48.811 --> 01:10:52.406
Our crew must've ended up there
after being shrunk!

01:10:52.515 --> 01:10:53.709
A cell?

01:10:53.816 --> 01:10:55.943
Yeah, of a human body.

01:10:56.052 --> 01:10:57.212
Whose?

01:10:57.587 --> 01:10:58.246
Yours!

01:10:58.354 --> 01:10:59.651
Mine?

01:10:59.922 --> 01:11:04.382
Let's just say! It was the leader's fault.

01:11:04.961 --> 01:11:10.524
His love for his girl,
his determination to find that planet,

01:11:10.633 --> 01:11:13.761
his desperation led the ship there.

01:11:14.671 --> 01:11:19.267
But one day, they realize
their bodies have grown bigger.

01:11:19.375 --> 01:11:20.637
Why?

01:11:20.777 --> 01:11:22.108
Wonder why!

01:11:23.880 --> 01:11:28.214
And they hear a voice! From inside your tummy
as you're sitting on the toilet.

01:11:28.318 --> 01:11:31.617
"Oh my God!
We're growing bigger and bigger!"

01:11:31.721 --> 01:11:33.552
Yikes!

01:11:33.656 --> 01:11:38.252
But they can communicate that way.
And they realize they're inside your stomach.

01:11:38.361 --> 01:11:39.623
- Then what?
- They've gotta get out!

01:11:39.729 --> 01:11:42.459
- From where?
- At this point, they're moving along the colon!

01:11:42.565 --> 01:11:43.793
Not happening!

01:11:44.067 --> 01:11:47.366
But what else can they do?
They keep getting bigger.

01:11:47.670 --> 01:11:48.694
Your belly'll explode!

01:11:48.805 --> 01:11:51.740
- I said no!
- "We're almost out, don't flush us!"

01:11:51.841 --> 01:11:53.365
I AM flushing them!

01:11:53.843 --> 01:11:55.811
"We're out! We're out!"

01:11:56.713 --> 01:11:58.237
NO!

01:13:44.987 --> 01:13:46.682
Myon!

01:13:46.789 --> 01:13:48.484
Nishi!

01:13:48.591 --> 01:13:52.357
Nishi! Myon!

01:13:52.795 --> 01:13:54.092
We're up here!

01:13:54.197 --> 01:13:55.824
You guys OK?

01:13:55.932 --> 01:13:57.559
A- OK!

01:13:58.067 --> 01:14:02.504
I'm relieved! We were worried!

01:14:02.605 --> 01:14:06.006
That was a surprise attack! So sudden!

01:14:24.060 --> 01:14:28.554
Told ya so! It's wicked, man!
A miracle, I say!

01:14:28.664 --> 01:14:32.259
<i>The Other World by Robin Nishi.
The guy's a fucking genius!</i>

01:14:32.902 --> 01:14:37.498
Cut class and meet me at the arcade!
The Strawberry Plaza in ten!

01:14:37.607 --> 01:14:39.006
Roger that.

01:14:39.342 --> 01:14:42.140
This place's so commercial.

01:14:42.745 --> 01:14:44.508
Dude, chill!

01:14:49.418 --> 01:14:50.908
Isn't that!

01:14:51.087 --> 01:14:54.079
Robin Nishi!

01:14:55.057 --> 01:14:57.082
<i>"R! Nishi Book Signing"</i>

01:14:57.226 --> 01:14:59.421
Check out the chicks!

01:14:59.529 --> 01:15:01.588
Fuckin' cool!

01:15:01.697 --> 01:15:04.325
Excuse me, you're Robin Nishi, right?

01:15:04.433 --> 01:15:06.594
Hiroshi, you idiot!

01:15:09.105 --> 01:15:10.094
Fuck yeah!

01:15:22.485 --> 01:15:23.782
Sorry!

01:15:24.053 --> 01:15:25.179
We're huge fans!

01:15:25.288 --> 01:15:28.018
<i>The Other World rocks!</i>

01:15:30.960 --> 01:15:32.894
Wanna grab a bite?

01:15:33.162 --> 01:15:34.026
Follow me!

01:15:34.130 --> 01:15:35.859
Seriously?!

01:15:38.768 --> 01:15:39.462
Eat!

01:15:39.569 --> 01:15:41.537
Yes!

01:15:42.438 --> 01:15:44.872
- This is like, your average day?
- Yeah!

01:15:44.974 --> 01:15:48.375
- Awesome!
- I feel so alive!

01:15:48.477 --> 01:15:50.672
Robin, I'll pick up the tab!

01:15:50.913 --> 01:15:52.380
What're you talking about?

01:15:52.481 --> 01:15:53.880
Hiroshi, you idiot!

01:15:59.555 --> 01:16:03.013
Hiroshi, kids shouldn't worry
about things like that.

01:16:03.259 --> 01:16:05.352
Have fun and become a man!

01:16:06.162 --> 01:16:09.723
Not a clone, but someone who transcends!

01:16:16.672 --> 01:16:19.641
<i>First contact with aliens!</i>

01:16:19.742 --> 01:16:25.271
<i>And directing this epic moment
is the artist who made it all possible!</i>

01:16:25.381 --> 01:16:29.044
<i>Salvatore Antonio Yang Gogh!</i>

01:16:44.834 --> 01:16:48.463
<i>"HELLO"</i>

01:16:48.938 --> 01:16:54.274
<i>The crowd's cheers've gone up a notch here
at the 1st Cosmic Swimming Contest.</i>

01:16:54.377 --> 01:16:57.710
<i>Representing Earth!
Matt Beyond Thorpe Myon!</i>

01:16:59.949 --> 01:17:04.409
<i>And so the race begins
as we witness history in the making!</i>

01:17:07.289 --> 01:17:11.749
<i>1st corner and into the gate!
Cameras are not allowed inside!</i>

01:17:19.702 --> 01:17:22.728
And they're coming out! 4 in the first group!
And she's there!

01:17:22.838 --> 01:17:25.932
<i>Matt Beyond Thorpe Myon,
representing Earth!</i>

01:17:29.078 --> 01:17:31.478
Isn't this supposed to be extinct?

01:17:36.185 --> 01:17:37.243
This one too!

01:19:04.790 --> 01:19:10.228
<i>"To Yang & Myon"</i>

01:19:35.154 --> 01:19:36.121
Think we can get out of here?

01:19:36.221 --> 01:19:37.245
Want to?

01:19:37.690 --> 01:19:40.352
We might be happier here.

01:19:58.544 --> 01:19:59.841
Jump!

01:20:21.433 --> 01:20:25.529
That's odd and it wasn't even time yet.

01:20:28.307 --> 01:20:32.334
Good God! I was about to go fetch you!

01:20:36.315 --> 01:20:37.441
Gramps.

01:20:37.549 --> 01:20:39.210
What's going on?

01:20:44.656 --> 01:20:47.750
The water level's increasing.

01:20:48.594 --> 01:20:51.722
And he's eating less.

01:20:52.164 --> 01:20:53.529
Meaning?

01:20:55.667 --> 01:20:59.899
Can't say for sure, but he could be dying.

01:21:00.506 --> 01:21:04.738
Dying? But what happens to us then?

01:21:05.144 --> 01:21:07.669
Eventually, this place'll sink.

01:21:10.716 --> 01:21:13.776
We've gotta leave. It's that or drown.

01:21:13.886 --> 01:21:15.444
But how?

01:21:15.554 --> 01:21:17.317
The boat, of course!

01:21:17.422 --> 01:21:20.255
- The cops'll be looking for us.
- So?

01:21:20.359 --> 01:21:22.827
The Yakuza'll come after us!

01:21:22.928 --> 01:21:25.522
So what! I wanna get out!

01:21:26.331 --> 01:21:28.060
'Cos there's so much out there!

01:21:28.167 --> 01:21:31.432
So many different people,
living different lives!

01:21:31.537 --> 01:21:34.097
Incredibly good guys, bad guys!

01:21:34.206 --> 01:21:38.267
Folks completely different from us!
It's one huge melting pot!

01:21:38.677 --> 01:21:43.011
See, it's not about success,
dying in the streets, who's better, who's not!

01:21:43.115 --> 01:21:45.345
I just want to be a part of it!

01:21:45.584 --> 01:21:49.076
I realized that even if I've no connections,
no talent,

01:21:49.254 --> 01:21:51.188
even if I'm one big loser,

01:21:51.290 --> 01:21:56.023
I want to use my hands and feet to think
and move, to shape my own life!

01:21:56.728 --> 01:22:00.755
We can just die here or we can try!

01:22:00.866 --> 01:22:03.596
See what we've got!

01:22:06.405 --> 01:22:10.808
It's impossible.
Motivation's not gonna get us over that wave.

01:22:11.243 --> 01:22:12.972
We need a motor boat!

01:22:16.415 --> 01:22:18.042
We've got a motor!

01:22:18.283 --> 01:22:19.682
Right here!

01:22:22.521 --> 01:22:23.988
But there's no fuel!

01:22:25.023 --> 01:22:28.959
Sure there is!
We came here by car, remember?

01:22:34.666 --> 01:22:35.325
Yes!

01:22:35.434 --> 01:22:36.264
It could work!

01:22:36.368 --> 01:22:37.665
It will work!

01:22:41.773 --> 01:22:44.173
We're going to make it!

01:22:44.743 --> 01:22:46.677
We're so gonna make it!

01:22:47.679 --> 01:22:48.976
Get up there!

01:23:48.473 --> 01:23:52.034
<i>The World Cup ends tomorrow
with its final match!</i>

01:23:52.144 --> 01:23:55.238
<i>As the world awaits to find out
who'll be the winner!</i>

01:23:55.514 --> 01:23:57.505
We're near Osaka again!

01:23:57.616 --> 01:23:58.275
Oh, yeah!

01:23:58.383 --> 01:24:01.784
I think this is our only chance!

01:24:01.987 --> 01:24:06.788
Maybe the whale's come here for us!

01:24:07.025 --> 01:24:08.754
And we're going for it!

01:24:40.592 --> 01:24:43.584
You're older. Lend it to her!

01:24:43.929 --> 01:24:45.226
I don't want to!

01:24:45.330 --> 01:24:46.228
Yang.

01:24:46.331 --> 01:24:49.232
Don't run like that, Myon'll follow you.

01:24:49.334 --> 01:24:51.063
Sorry, Myon!

01:24:53.171 --> 01:24:55.196
I don't like that uniform!

01:24:55.540 --> 01:24:57.474
- I'll work!
- Sorry Yang!

01:25:04.983 --> 01:25:06.041
Wanna try?

01:25:13.892 --> 01:25:14.859
Myon.

01:25:24.236 --> 01:25:25.567
Yang!

01:25:26.405 --> 01:25:27.929
Thanks!

01:25:29.007 --> 01:25:31.942
I'm not gonna let you carry
all the load anymore!

01:25:32.044 --> 01:25:33.909
I'll grow up.

01:25:35.147 --> 01:25:36.580
I'm sorry.

01:25:36.681 --> 01:25:40.947
I always knew you were the one
that needed support.

01:25:43.955 --> 01:25:47.618
It's your turn now!

01:25:47.993 --> 01:25:50.427
Go ahead!

01:26:17.556 --> 01:26:20.525
Here we go kids!

01:26:22.094 --> 01:26:25.325
Yes sir!

01:27:32.597 --> 01:27:36.556
Run!

01:28:09.501 --> 01:28:10.991
Water striders float!

01:28:11.102 --> 01:28:15.095
Using surface tension
from the hairs on their legs.

01:28:38.129 --> 01:28:38.857
I'm sorry.

01:29:08.226 --> 01:29:11.320
Your bones won't get strong
if you don't drink milk.

01:29:11.429 --> 01:29:12.794
Yes, mom!

01:29:18.637 --> 01:29:21.162
Ah, not again!

01:29:21.806 --> 01:29:23.933
I'll put it in your food then!

01:33:18.009 --> 01:33:20.409
This'll be perfect.

01:33:21.546 --> 01:33:24.310
- Hey, wrong nail!
- The baby!

01:33:24.415 --> 01:33:27.976
- You OK?
- It's heavy!

01:33:28.086 --> 01:33:29.417
There!

01:33:29.921 --> 01:33:33.015
Mmm, too much space for a little kid!

01:33:33.124 --> 01:33:35.115
Ah, he'll be big in no time!

01:33:35.393 --> 01:33:37.691
Wonder what he'll be like.

01:33:42.200 --> 01:33:44.600
Be right there, sweetie!

01:33:45.103 --> 01:33:48.971
Your fever's just gone down, you know.

01:33:49.073 --> 01:33:49.903
I'm fine.

01:33:50.008 --> 01:33:51.771
See you later!

01:33:52.510 --> 01:33:53.772
See you at 10!

01:33:54.445 --> 01:33:56.037
Keiko? It's me!

01:33:56.614 --> 01:33:59.447
Myon? I've got an art show.

01:33:59.651 --> 01:34:00.948
That's great!

01:34:01.286 --> 01:34:02.878
<i>And she's going for the rope!</i>

01:34:02.987 --> 01:34:03.885
<i>"A Lonely Death"</i>

01:34:03.988 --> 01:34:05.956
We've got no money either!

01:34:06.991 --> 01:34:07.719
<i>Worn by!</i>

01:34:11.429 --> 01:34:12.123
There, found it!

01:34:12.230 --> 01:34:12.889
Jun!

01:34:13.431 --> 01:34:14.398
Hi!

01:34:15.567 --> 01:34:17.398
That's insane! They're Yakuzas!

01:34:17.735 --> 01:34:22.138
I told you to wait till tomorrow,
so shut up and wait, you punk!

01:34:23.308 --> 01:34:26.835
Sorry about that! Now back to your interview!

01:35:03.147 --> 01:35:04.307
That's her!

01:35:29.841 --> 01:35:31.172
Myon!

